<p>Using <a href="http://www.dropzonejs.com/" rel="nofollow">dropzone.js</a>, I'm running into an issue when I submit my form. Here is my code:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>items.coffee </p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>  $('#new_item').dropzone     acceptedFiles: '.jpeg, .jpg, .png'     maxFilesize: 1     maxFiles: 100     addRemoveLinks: true     paramName: 'item[image]'     clickable: '#image-preview'     headers: "X-CSRF-Token" : $('meta[name="csrf-token"]').attr('content')     previewsContainer: '#image-preview'     thumbnailWidth: 300     thumbnailHeight: 300     autoProcessQueue: false     uploadMultiple: true     parallelUploads: 100     init: -&gt;       myDropzone = this       @element.querySelector('#item-submit').addEventListener 'click', (e) -&gt;         e.preventDefault()         e.stopPropagation()         if myDropzone.getQueuedFiles().length &gt; 0           myDropzone.processQueue()         else           $("#new_item").submit();         return       @on 'sendingmultiple', -&gt;         return       @on 'successmultiple', (files, response) -&gt;         return       @on 'errormultiple', (files, response) -&gt;         return       return </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>items_controller.rb</p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>class ItemsController &lt; ApplicationController    def continue     @item = Item.find(params[:id])     if @item.user_id == current_user.id     else       redirect_to root_path     end   end    def new     @item = current_user.items.build   end    def create     @item = current_user.items.build(item_params)      if @item.save       redirect_to post_continue_item_path(@item)     else       render :new        render json: @item.errors, status: :unprocessable_entity     end      end     private    def item_params     params.require(:item).permit(:name, :description, :image)   end    def find_item     @item = Item.find(params[:id])   end  end </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>routes.rb</p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>  resources :items do     collection do       get 'lost', to: 'items#index_lost'       get 'found', to: 'items#index_found'     end     get '/post/continue', to: 'items#continue', on: :member   end </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>items/_form.haml</p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>= form_for @item, validate: true, html: {multipart: true} do |f|     = f.label :name, class: 'col-lg-2 control-label'         = f.text_field :name     %main#image-preview         .fallback         = f.file_field :image, multiple: false     .submit-section         .col-lg-12.col-md-12             = f.submit 'Done', id: 'item-submit' </code></pre>  <p>So to add more detail, if I drag and drop or upload a file to the Dropzone, it will allow it and since <code>autoProcessQueue</code> is false it doesn't submit the form automatically but instead waits for the submit button to be clicked. Well that occurs but than I get this error inside of the uploaded image on hover over:</p>  <pre><code>ActionView::MissingTemplate - Missing template items/continue, application/continue with {:locale=&gt;[:en], :formats=&gt;[:json], :variants=&gt;[], :handlers=&gt;[:erb, :builder, :raw, :ruby, :coffee, :arb, :haml, :jbuilder]}. Searched in: </code></pre>  <p>(full error here: <a href="https://gist.github.com/justintech/52a0bbf0e795bbcc3a04" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/justintech/52a0bbf0e795bbcc3a04</a>)</p>  <p>I have a template called <code>items/continue.html.erb</code> but I think the issue is that Dropzone is uploading the file before the form is submitted. Not sure so I'm here for help. How would I solve this problem or what would you do?</p>